    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup is anchored by the elite efficiency of **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who carries an 80.96 score into his matchup against Spencer Arrighetti. The combination of a favorable 5.10 xERA and a 100% stolen base opportunity window against this specific starter makes **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** our priority start. Joining him at the top of the board is **Lawrence Butler** (65.53), whose aggressive platoon advantage against Emerson Hancock outweighs the inherent volatility of an #8 lineup position. **Bryson Stott** (64.41) and **Taylor Ward** (63.61) also grade out as strong plays; **Taylor Ward** benefits significantly from wind conditions and a leadoff spot, while **Bryson Stott** finds value despite an elite opposing hold pitcher because his dynamic platoon edge against Colin Rea is too high to ignore.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved the utility spot, where **Yainer Diaz** (52.02) narrowly edged out **Gleyber Torres** (41.31). While **Gleyber Torres** holds theoretical appeal, the optimizer penalized his projected efficiency due to a suboptimal matchup against Sonny Gray and a high negative impact from the platoon split. **Yainer Diaz** remains the safer, higher-floor play for today\u2019s volume. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on **Daulton Varsho** (41.43); he is currently at the bottom of our starters due to a difficult matchup against Reid Detmers and his struggles against left-handed pitching, making him the first candidate to be pulled should we need to protect our daily game caps.\n\nRisks remain elevated as we navigate \"Lineup Pending\" statuses for the bulk of our roster. We are particularly cautious regarding the projections for **Will Smith**, who currently sits at a 74.95 score; if he is shifted out of the #3 hole in the official lineup, we will see a rapid decline in that efficiency. Furthermore, while **Tyler Freeman** holds a 51.80 score thanks to his speed profile against a slow-delivery pitcher, his matchup against Justin Wrobleski is thin. We are maintaining current bench depth with **Geraldo Perdomo**, **Matt Chapman**, **Luis Arraez**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Gavin Sheets**, and **Drew Gilbert** in reserve to ensure we can pivot if weather alerts or sudden late-scratch notifications impact our projected starters.",
